===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|quaveren}}, frequentative form of {{m|enm|quaven}}, {{m|enm|cwavien||to tremble}}, equivalent to {{suffix|quave|er|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nds|-}} {{m|nds|quabbeln||to quiver}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{m|de|quabbeln}}, {{m|de|quappeln||to quiver}}. More at {{l|en|quave}}, {{l|en|quab}}, {{l|en|quiver}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|eɪvə(r)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a [[trembling]] shake.
# a trembling of the voice, as in speaking or singing.
# {{label|en|music}} an [[eighth note]], drawn as a [[crotchet]] ([[quarter note]]) with a tail.

